Iowa Winter Road Conditions. Conditions have been archived every 30 minutes during the winter season (October 15 to April 15). Data archived by Iowa DOT GIS team on behalf of the Office of Traffic Operations. Current archived winter seasons are 2015-2016 and 2016-2017.

portalName: Winter Storm Analysis - Past 48 Hours (High Availability Feature Collection)
column3: Winter Storm Analysis InformationThis service contains the aggregated, material usage, labor, equipment and related costs for maintaining Iowa DOT's road network during winter snow events for the past 48 hours. Data is derived from the snowplow AVL/GPS data feeds. ?This data is used for Iowa DOT's Winter Cost Calculator Application.?This data is updated every 15 minutes.?Note: All values estimated based on best-available data.Note: This is an Esri Feature Collection which is different than an Esri Feature Service. Feature Collections allow for high-availability. There are unique characteristics that need to be considered when using this data type:?It is a file-based data type so there is no REST endpoint. However, there is JSON that can be parsed out. See link at the bottom of this page.You cannot set a refresh interval in the map document, you must use the Info Summary Widget inside an application or hard-code the refresh in a custom application.The rotation setting gets wiped out each time the dataset is updated. When you add a feature collection to a new map, you will have to set the rotation. If you have an existing saved map this doesn?t apply to you.
